@startuml
actor Admin
actor User
participant Frontend
participant Backend
database DB

== Seeding ==
Admin -> Frontend: Access Admin UI
Frontend -> Backend: Submit seed data
Backend -> DB: Insert schools, departments,\nprograms, courses, teachers,\nsemesters, sections
Backend -> Backend: Validate seeded data
alt Invalid data
    Backend -> Frontend: Notify admin of issues
    Frontend -> Admin: Display issues
else Valid
    Backend -> Frontend: Data is live
end

== User Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Sign up / Log in
Frontend -> Backend: Register / Authenticate
Backend -> DB: Insert / Query user
Backend -> Frontend: Return session

User -> Frontend: Create calendar
Frontend -> Backend: POST calendar
Backend -> DB: Insert calendar

User -> Frontend: Add calendar semester\n(pick program + semester)
Frontend -> Backend: POST calendar_semester
Backend -> DB: Insert calendars_semesters

loop Add / Remove sections
    User -> Frontend: Add or remove section
    Frontend -> Backend: POST / DELETE calendars_semesters_sections
    Backend -> DB: Insert / Delete section
    Backend -> Backend: Evaluate rules\n(prerequisites, corequisites,\nmutexes, unit caps,\nfixed electives, major quota)
    Backend -> Frontend: Return issues list (non-blocking)
    Frontend -> User: Display flagged issues
end

@enduml
